                        "content": "A newly admitted client is exhibiting signs and symptoms associated with a loss of physical functioning, although no such loss can be confirmed medically. This situation supports which mental health diagnosis?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nEmotional turmoil expressed in physical signs is the hallmark of somatization disorder. None of the other options are associated with loss of physical function.\n\nClient Needs: Psychosocial Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Recognize Cues\nCognitive Ability: Analyzing\nContent Area: Mental Health\nHealth Problem: Mental Health: Somatization Disorder\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Assessment\nPriority Concepts: Psychosis, Clinical Judgment\nStrategies: Subject\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, the characteristics associated with somatization disorder. Recall that physical signs with no real basis are the major feature of somatization disorder; this will direct you to the correct option.\n ",
                        "id": "54216ef302d6491b99230317f7aaaae1",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "8fbb79d1510d4fcd832037b326129730",
                                "content": "Refer the client to a psychiatrist."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "82cf7b94d8b44761a63f88e9673e7cc2",
                                "content": "Encourage the client to move and use the arm."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "d434beac4d954146ad3e90d68793bead",
                                "content": "Assess the client for organic causes of the paralysis."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "2454435133bf4c5fae0346f4b883a118",
                                "content": "Encourage the client to talk about his or her feelings.\n"
                            }
                        ],
