                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "A nurse is performing an assessment on a client being admitted to the mental health unit. During the interview, the nurse discovers that the client suffered a severe emotional trauma 1 month earlier and is now experiencing paralysis of the right arm. Which is the initial nursing action?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nThe initial nursing action would be to assess for any physiological causes of the paralysis. Although the client may be referred to a psychiatrist, this is not the initial action. It is inappropriate to encourage the client to use the arm without ruling out a physiological cause of the paralysis. Although a component of the plan of care would be to encourage the client to discuss feelings, this would not be the initial nursing action.\n\nClient Needs: Physiological Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Take Action\nCognitive Ability: Applying\nContent Area: Mental Health\nHealth Problem: Mental Health: Somatization Disorder\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Implementation\nPriority Concepts: Clinical Judgment, Safety\nStrategies: Maslow's Hierarchy of Needs Theory, Strategic Words\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the strategic word, initial. Use Maslow's Hierarchy of Needs theory to answer the question. Remember that physiological needs are the first priority. The correct option is the only one that addresses a physiological need.",
                        "id": "5e4acd6a51444cf4a54225f16374a9ba",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "427d0a914dda4bfe906885411356e369",
                                "content": "Psychosis "
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "bfe49acdbe1d45e0a421b2ce8b396620",
                                "content": "Repression"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "c1f9bec78e9440d684afa0a885c1412c",
                                "content": "Conversion disorder"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "a3d4128fbf8a4fc8b299dea323c6971d",
                                "content": "Dissociative disorder"
                            }
                        ],
